<plot>This documentary series travels to modern Vietnam to tell the stories of four different young Vietnamese people and their thoughts about the present and future of their country. One is a fashion designer with Western ideas about designs, another is a police agent-turned-artist, the third is a photographer with a taste for the aesthetics of the body, and the last one is a DJ of techno music. They speak of the duality between Eastern belongings and Western inspirations and of the difficulties of living in a Communist regime.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?378108</url></doc>
